RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Marysville, WA operates under a mayor-council form of government. The Mayor and seven City Council members are elected at-large for four-year terms. The City Council also selects one of its members to serve as Council President. As of November 21, 2025, the listed officials are currently serving. Recent election results from November 6, 2025, indicate some incumbents were re-elected and a new council member for Position 3, Dan Perkins, holds a lead, but the official city website still lists Tom King for Position 3. The JSON reflects the officials currently listed on the official city website.
